{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "26", "m": "03", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "12", "M": "46", "S": "58"}}, "news": [{"title": "Madras HC issues notice to Tamil Nadu on PIL against layout approvals in hill areas", "para": "An activist has approached the Madras High Court challenging a Tamil Nadu government order. This order empowers urban planning authorities to approve housing layouts in hill areas. It bypasses the mandatory clearance from the Hill Area Conservation Authority (HACA). The petitioner argues this dilutes environmental safeguards and could cause ecological damage.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/madras-hc-notice-to-tamil-nadu-on-controversial-housing-approvals-in-hills/129819940?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-50334/129819940.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Under smart city mission, over 357 projects worth over \u20b911,000 crore completed in Gujarat", "para": "With an extensive network of roads and railways, along with the development of international airports and ports, Gujarat today has a well-developed transport network that provides excellent connectivity to its citizens. To manage the increasing traffic in urban areas efficiently, overbridges and underbridges are being constructed across the state. In particular, in the four major cities, Ahmedabad, Rajkot, Vadodara, and Surat, a strong road network is being developed through such infrastructure, making transportation easier for citizens.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/smart-city/gujarats-urban-transformation-pm-modi-to-inaugurate-11000-crore-projects/129819903?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-99266/129819903.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "smart-city"}, {"title": "About 34% of 72 lakh Karnataka homes